CompiledTemplateBuilder Class

Definition

An ITemplate implementation that is called from the generated page class code. This class cannot be inherited.

In this Article

public sealed class CompiledTemplateBuilder : System.Web.UI.ITemplate
Inheritance
System.Object
CompiledTemplateBuilder

Inherited Members

Equals(Object)
Equals(Object,Object)
GetHashCode()
GetType()
MemberwiseClone()
ReferenceEquals(Object,Object)
ToString()

Remarks

The CompiledTemplateBuilder class is used by ASP.NET to create a template for a templated control from the generated class code. It is not meant to be used directly in your code.

Constructors

CompiledTemplateBuilder(BuildTemplateMethod)

Initializes a new instance of the CompiledTemplateBuilder class.

public CompiledTemplateBuilder (System.Web.UI.BuildTemplateMethod buildTemplateMethod);
buildTemplateMethod
BuildTemplateMethod

A delegate used to handle the stem.Web.UI.CompiledTemplateBuilder.InstantiateIn* method call.

Remarks

This constructor is used internally by ASP.NET to create a new instance of the CompiledTemplateBuilder class. It is not meant to be used directly in your code.

Methods

InstantiateIn(Control)

Populates the Control object with the child controls contained in the template.

public void InstantiateIn (System.Web.UI.Control container);
container
Control

A Control that represents the container used to store the child controls in the template.

Remarks

The InstantiateIn method is the TemplateBuilder class's implementation of the InstantiateIn method. It is used by ASP.NET to create the control hierarchy of the template and is not meant to be used directly in your code.
